cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper introduces a game between a controller and an attacker, where the controller uses a new formulation of model-predictive control. The paper also discusses the controllability of the system. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper discusses the interaction between a controller and an attacker, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper introduces a new formulation of model-predictive control and discusses the strategies of both naive and intelligent attackers. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper uses a simple model of flocking dynamics as the plant in the V-formation game. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper introduces a game between a controller and an attacker, and discusses the strategies of both players.
